# The Void

The Void is a premium private capital command platform — an operator-grade system for capital overview, market intelligence, opportunity evaluation, strategy control, inventory management, risk control, execution lifecycle visibility, replay/lab simulation, and audit/admin governance.

It is NOT a retail exchange, wallet, generic admin panel, or toy dashboard.

## Workflow Discipline

- **Inspect before changing.** Summarize what exists, what can be reused, and what is missing. State the exact phase before generating code.
- **Change only what is necessary.** Do not touch unrelated files. Prefer incremental changes over large rewrites. Do not rename or rewrite major parts without strong reason.
- **Build phase by phase.** Work in controlled implementation phases. Finish the current phase, then stop. Provide a short verification checklist after each phase.

## Architecture

- Monorepo: `apps/web`, `apps/api`, shared packages.
- Controllers stay thin. Business logic lives in services/core modules.
- Shared types are centralized.
- Explicit state machines where lifecycle matters.
- No giant files, no hidden magic.

## Coding Standards

- Strongly typed TypeScript everywhere.
- Clear naming, small cohesive modules.
- Honest mocks and simulations — no fake production claims, no dead abstractions, no duplicated type systems.
- Code must compile, imports must resolve, routes/modules must register, schema/types must stay aligned. State limitations honestly.

## Product & UX

- Operator-first information architecture. Build for operators, treasury users, analysts, strategy users, and admins.
- Prioritize clarity, control, explainability, and premium execution UX.
- Do not turn the UI into generic SaaS or crypto-casino styling. The design must feel premium, institutional, and dense-but-readable.

## Visual System

| Token | Value |
|---|---|
| Background | Warm off-white / subtle cream |
| Text | Super dark purple (not black) |
| Primary accent | Bright refined orange |
| Positive/healthy | Mint-cyan / blue-green |
| Style | Elegant borders, subtle shadows, excellent tables, premium cards |

## Backend Realism

- Use lawful, documented, auditable infrastructure only.
- Use mock connectors and simulated venues in MVP where needed.
- Data must be plausible, not random nonsense.
- Expose typed APIs and consistent websocket events.
